### Centered Galaxy Creation Techniques:
# 1. Use very large scale (800-1200) for background to create uniform deep space
# 2. Use progressively smaller scales: core (300-500) → arms (180-250) → details (80-150)
# 3. High persistence (0.8-0.95) on core layer for bright center (SCREEN/ADD blend)
# 4. Medium persistence (0.6-0.7) on arms layer for structure (OVERLAY blend)
# 5. Low persistence (0.4-0.5) on detail layers for subtle features (SOFT_LIGHT)
# 6. Use RIDGED noise with MULTIPLY blend for dust lanes (opacity 0.3-0.4)
# 7. Dark color palette (#000000 to #ffffff) with narrow thresholds (0.05-0.1 and 0.9-0.95)
# 8. Experiment with different seeds to find interesting spiral patterns
# 9. All examples use 4000x4000 resolution for high detail
# 10. Layer seed offsets help create distinct patterns for each component